The best approach involves understanding user needs, choosing the technology stack, and partnering
                    with an experienced development team. Agile methodologies ensure flexibility and faster delivery.
The cost depends on project complexity, features, and development time. Smaller projects may cost
                    less, while larger budgets require custom solutions with advanced functionalities.
Outsourcing offers cost savings, access to global talent, and quicker project delivery. It also
                    allows businesses to focus on core operations while experts handle technical aspects.
Look for a company with a proven track record, strong expertise in your industry, and excellent
                    communication. Reviews, portfolios, and client testimonials are also key factors.
Building an MVP (Minimum Viable Product) allows businesses to test their idea in the market quickly,
                    gather user feedback, and reduce development risks before scaling.
